name: Event °_°
description:
And there she and I were /
like smoke in the dark /
fleeting yet there.

No words /
just a fond glance /
as I gave my hand.

Three months later /
we rolled towels like soldiers /
kicked carts like horses /
then the glass panel /
cut deeper than a crescent wave /
and I fought for air /
that didn’t move.

As we held our noses /
That screeched to a halt /
arms pulled us away /
Just so much flesh and blood /
vaporized into steam /
helpless to save /
her whom I loved.
